wiki.content:
"You" is a song by Radiohead from their debut album "Pablo Honey. A love song of an obsessive nature that first appeared on the Manic Hedgehog demo. This version was included on the Drill EP. For Pablo Honey, the song was rerecorded and some of the lyrics changed. The song greatly showcases Thom Yorke's tenor voice with him belting C5 during the guitar solo. Performed live, the song is an excellent showcase for Thom's incredible vocal abilities; he holds one note throughout the guitar solo.

comments: Simply you have to love it... One of their best songs...
And why should I believe myself not you?
This is a surprisingly good song.
Música foda , acho até melhor que Creep .
Esta canción es mucho mejor que Creep...
I get chills listening to this 1 - incredible!
the only song i like on pablo honey.
This song should have been on an EP all its own. It's far stronger than anything else on Pablo Honey.

Pablo Honey basically proves that Radiohead could be a great band without all the studio creativity. Great straight ahead rock. Normal guitar solo. Normal drumming. Normal rock vocals. 

If they pulled a U2 and went back to being a straight ahead rock band, I think they'd pull it off better than U2 did. And that's a high bar (of course, they pulled off the complete left turn into electronic music 1000 times better than U2).
my favorite track from Pablo Honey
great song.  I wonder if Radiohead will every do another album without all the electronic stuff.  I bet it would be killer
